{
  "doc_id": "17917",
  "text": "In the current study, we did not find a significant difference in disruption of odontoblastic layer between the studied groups. This can be the result of applying light force in our study. In contrast, Ramazanzadeh et al. [CITATION_1] reported more cases with odontoblastic layer disruption in the intrusive group compared to controls. Mostafa et al. [CITATION_2] reported that disruption of odontoblastic layer is associated with pulpal blood flow changes.",
